"51.32","c":"فِي","d":"fàِ","e":"fī"},{"b":"32.9","h":"51.77","c":"سَبِيلِي","d":"sbَyِlàِ","e":"sabīlī"},{"b":"34.0","h":"53.06","c":"وَابْتِغَاءَ","d":"wbٱَtْغِāَءَٓ","e":"wa-ib'tighāa"},{"b":"36.6","h":"55.42","c":"مَرْضَاتِي","d":"mrَḍْāَtàِ","e":"marḍātī"},{"b":"38.3","h":"58.7","c":"تُسِرُّونَ","d":"tsُrِwُّnَ","e":"tusirrūna"},{"b":"39.4","h":"59.82","c":"إِلَيْهِمْ","d":"ʾilِyَhْmِ","e":"ilayhim"},{"b":"40.9","h":"61.32","c":"بِالْمَوَدَّةِ","d":"blٱِmْwَdَẗَِّ","e":"bil-mawadati"},{"b":"42.2","h":"62.95","c":"وَأَنَا","d":"wʾَanَāَ۠","e":"wa-anā"},{"b":"42.","h":"63.61","c":"أَعْلَمُ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْmَُ","e":"aʿlamu"},{"b":"43.5","h":"64.59","c":"بِمَا","d":"bmِāَٓ","e":"bimā"},{"b":"45.3","h":"65.94","c":"أَخْفَيْتُمْ","d":"ʾakَhfْyَtْmُْ","e":"akhfaytum"},{"b":"46.5","h":"67.67","c":"وَمَا","d":"wmَāَٓ","e":"wamā"},{"b":"47.","h":"68.46","c":"أَعْلَنْتُمْ","d":"ʾaعَʿlْnَtmُْ","e":"aʿlantum"},{"b":"51.0","h":"74.15","c":"وَمَنْ","d":"wmَnَ","e":"waman"},{"b":"52.3","h":"75.16","c":"يَفْعَلْهُ","d":"yfَعْʿlَhُْ","e":"yafʿalhu"},{"b":"53.1","h":"76.42","c":"مِنْكُمْ","d":"mnِkmُْ","e":"minkum"},{"b":"54.4","h":"77.93","c":"فَقَدْ","d":"fqَdَْ","e":"faqad"},{"b":"55.0","h":"78.51","c":"ضَلَّ","d":"ḍlََّ","e":"ḍalla"},{"b":"55.6","h":"79.25","c":"سَوَاءَ","d":"swَāَءَٓ","e":"sawāa"},{"b":"57.9","h":"81.2","c":"السَّبِيلِ","d":"lٱsbَّyِlِ","e":"l-sabīli"}],"a":{"g":"O you who have believed, do not take My enemies and your enemies as allies, extending to them affection while they have disbelieved in what came to you of the truth, having driven out the Prophet and yourselves [only] because you believe in Allah, your Lord. If you have come out for jihad in My cause and seeking means to My approval, [take them not as friends]. You confide to them affection, but I am most knowing of what you have concealed and what you have declared. And whoever does it among you has certainly strayed from the soundness of the way.","ihya":"\n        <div class=\"ihya-tafsir-box\" style=\"margin-top: 15px; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 10px;\">\n            <h5 style=\"color: #91740c; font-family: Cabin, sans-serif;\">Tafsir Al-Ihya</h5>\n            <div class=\"ihya-arabic\" style=\"font-family: IndoPak; font-size: 18px; text-align: right; margin-bottom: 10px; color: #555;\">\n                وقال عز وجل يَا أَيُّهَا الَّذِينَ آمَنُوا لَا تَتَّخِذُوا عَدُوِّي وَعَدُوَّكُمْ أَوْلِيَاءَ الآية. فأما الانبساط معه والاسترسال إليه كما يسترسل إلى الأصدقاء فهو مكروه كراهة شديدة يكاد ينتهي ما يقوى منها إلى حد التحريم قال تعالى لا تجد قوما يؤمنون بالله واليوم الآخر يوادون من حاد الله ورسوله ولو كانوا آباءهم أو أبناءهم الآية وقال صلى الله عليه وسلم المسلم والمشرك لا تتراءى ناراهما حديث المؤمن والمشرك لا تتراءى ناراهما رواه أبو داود و الترمذي من حديث جرير أنا بريء من كل مسلم يقيم بين أظهر المشركين قالوا يا رسول الله ولم قال لا تراءى ناراهما رواه النسائي مرسلا وقال البخاري الصحيح أنه مرسل وقال عز وجل يا أيها الذين آمنوا لا تتخذوا عدوي وعدوكم أولياء الآية.\n            </div>\n            <div class=\"ihya-english\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; text-align: justify; color: #777;\">\n                Indeed, He, the Mighty and Majestic, has said: \"O you who have believed, do not take My enemy and your enemy as allies [awliya']...\" (60:1). As for being at ease [al-inbisat] with him and being unreserved [al-istirsal] towards him, as one is unreserved with friends, then that is disliked [makruh] with a severe dislike, such that the strongest degree of it nearly reaches the limit of prohibition [tahrim]. He, the Exalted, has said: \"You will not find a people who believe in Allah and the Last Day having affection [yuwadduna] for those who oppose Allah and His Messenger, even if they were their fathers or their sons...\" (58:22). And He, peace and blessings be upon him, said: \"The Muslim and the polytheist [mushrik]—their fires [narahuma] should not be visible to one another.\" (A narration states: \"The believer [mu'min] and the polytheist—their fires should not be visible to one another.\") Abu Dawud and At-Tirmidhi narrated it from the hadith of Jarir: \"I am free from every Muslim who resides among the polytheists.\" They said, \"O Messenger of Allah, why?\" He said, \"Their fires should not be visible to one another.\" An-Nasa'i narrated it as mursal, and Al-Bukhari said the correct view is that it is mursal. And He, the Mighty and Majestic, has said: \"O you who have believed, do not take My enemy and your enemy as allies...\" (60:1).\n            </div>\n        </div>\n        "}},"2":{"w":[{"b":"0.03","h":"0","c":"إِنْ","d":"ʾinِ","e":"in"},{"b":"1.1","h":"1.89","c":"يَثْقَفُوكُمْ","d":"ytَhqْfَwُkmُْ","e":"yathqafūkum"},{"b":"2.3","h":"3.41","c":"يَكُونُوا","d":"ykَwُnwُā۟","e":"yakūnū"},{"b":"3.2","h":"4.55","c":"لَكُمْ","d":"lkَmُْ","e":"lakum"},{"b":"3.8","h":"5.26","c":"أَعْدَاءً","d":"ʾaعَʿdْāَءًٓ","e":"aʿdāan"},{"b":"6.6","h":"8.16","c":"وَيَبْسُطُوا","d":"wyَbَsْṭُwُāٓ۟","e":"wayabsuṭū"},{"b":"9.3","h":"10.3","c":"إِلَيْكُمْ","d":"ʾilِyَkْmُْ","e":"ilaykum"},{"b":"10.2","h":"11.38","c":"أَيْدِيَهُمْ","d":"ʾayَdْyِhَmُْ","e":"aydiyahum"},{"b":"11.4","h":"12.73","c":"وَأَلْسِنَتَهُمْ","d":"wʾَalَsْnِtَhَmُ","e":"wa-alsinatahum"},{"b":"13.5","h":"15.09","c":"بِالسُّوءِ","d":"blٱِswُّءِٓ","e":"bil-sūi"},{"b":"15.7","h":"17.11","c":"وَوَدُّوا","d":"wwَdَwُّā۟","e":"wawaddū"},{"b":"16.6","h":"18.27","c":"لَوْ","d":"lwَْ","e":"law"},{"b":"16.9","h":"18.54","c":"تَكْفُرُونَ","d":"tkَfْrُwُnَ","e":"takfurūna"}],"a":{"g":"If they gain dominance over you, they would be to you as enemies and extend against you their hands and their tongues with evil, and they wish you would disbelieve."}},"3":{"w":[{"b":"0.09","h":"0.31","c":"لَنْ","d":"lnَ","e":"lan"},{"b":"1.2","h":"1.32","c":"تَنْفَعَكُمْ","d":"tnَfعَʿkَmُْ","e":"tanfaʿakum"},{"b":"3.2","h":"3.54","c":"أَرْحَامُكُمْ","d":"ʾarَḥْāَmkُmُْ","e":"arḥāmukum"},{"b":"4.5","h":"5.21","c":"وَلَا","d":"wlَāَٓ","e":"walā"},{"b":"6.2","h":"7.41","c":"